Review: Mesmerized by the way objects fall out of the sky. Stuck in fate, stuck in omens, rituals, loves, pains. We're all the same. Some people seem to be born under the right star. A trick of the light? Destiny? It often feels like we can only pray for rain. It's hard to remember that we're made of water.

A mother's impossible task is to protect and guide her children. Even in the best of circumstances, a mother can only control so much. In the worst of circumstances what is one to even do? Children will find simple joys where they can. It can't be stopped. Their lives will blossom and extend faster than protections and safeguards can be put up around them. Sarbajaya does everything in her power to try and protect her children. I think most would…
